ParameterInfo.description: ItemRevision on which the latest references are added or updated.

List of the business objects of type Cae1OutOfDateObject. Cae1OutOfDateObject is a runtime business object. Cae1OutOfDateObject has a TypedReference property cae1OutOfDateObjectRef, which points to the ItemRevision. This operation searches for the latest revision of this referenced ItemRevision and attaches it to the context object either keeping the previous revision or removing it.
Flag to indicate if Add or Update Latest References operation has to be performed. If true, Add Latest References operation is performed; otherwise Update Latest References.

Operation.description:
This operation either adds or updates latest references(revisions) for an ItemRevision which is related to the context object. The context object is of type CAEAnalysisRevision or CAEModelRevision. CAEAnalysisRevision or CAEModelRevision has a status object Fnd0ObjectCheckStatus attached to it which stores the information of the secondary objects of the context object. “Mark up-to-date” action updates this information stored in the status object. If the context object has secondary object that is added, modified, removed or ItemRevision which is revised after marking context object as up-to-date, then the context object becomes out-of-date.
For out-of-date context object, a table is shown on Attachments sub-location listing all the Cae1OutOfDateObject runtime objects which hold a reference of the secondary objects. By selecting one or more objects from the table, addOrUpdateLatestReferences operation is invoked which either attaches the latest revision of the secondary object to the context object with the same relation keeping the previous revision as it is or replaces the previous revision with the latest one.
Operation.name: addOrUpdateLatestReferences
Operation.returnDescription:
This operation returns serviceData. serviceData contains created and deleted objects (e.g. added or deleted relations) along with partial errors if any.
Following partial errors may be returned:

35009 - The relation does not exist.
35011 - The Relation cannot be deleted.
39014 - The specified type does not exist.
89001 - The creation of relation failed.
89009 - Exceeding secondary object cardinality.
89010 - Exceeding primary object cardinality.
Operation.useCase:
The Add Latest References and Update Latest References commands are available on Active Workspace Client.

Use Case 1: Open a CAEAnalysisRevision. Go to Attachments sub-location. “Out-of-date objects” table is displayed. Select one or more out-of-date objects and execute command Add Latest References.

Use Case 2: Open a CAEAnalysisRevision. Go to Attachments sub-location. “Out-of-date objects” table is displayed. Select one or more out-of-date objects and execute command Update Latest References.

Use Case 3: Open a CAEModelRevision. Go to Attachments sub-location. “Out-of-date objects” table is displayed. Select one or more out-of-date objects and execute command Add Latest References.

Use Case 4: Open a CAEModelRevision. Go to Attachments sub-location. “Out-of-date objects” table is displayed. Select one or more out-of-date objects and execute command Update Latest References.

Operation.description:
This operation checks if the input object(CAEModelRevision or CAEAnalysisRevision) is Out-of-date. The operation returns true/false based on the conditions below:
1. If CAE Status property value is Up-to-date or N/A, then operation returns false.
2. If CAE Status property value is Out-of-date due to dependent attachments, the operation returns true.
3. If CAE Status property value is Out-of-date only due to new revisions of dependent item revisions, the operation returns false.

ParameterInfo.description: The input object (CAEModelRevision or CAEAnalysisRevision) in context for which CAE Status details will be retrieved.

Operation.description:
This operation retrieves the CAE Status and out-of-date details of the input object (CAEModelRevision or CAEAnalysisRevision) in context. The out-of-date details consists of:

1. Count of dependent objects added, modified or removed for input object in context.
2. Count of dependent ItemRevision objects having a newer revision.

If data is found for any of the conditions mentioned above, the CAE Status of input object is considered as “Out-of-date”, or “Up-to-date” in case no dependent objects are found.
Operation.name: getCAEStatusDetails
Operation.returnDescription:
This response contains the information needed to show under CAE Status Summary section under Simulation XRT page in Active Workspace.
The following partial errors may be returned:
• 206649 - Unknown attribute found.
• 35003 - The provided Relation type is invalid.
• 515024 - The given object does not exist in the database or is not a persistent object.
• 515033 - The given value is invalid
Operation.useCase:
In Active Workspace Client, user navigates to the Simulation XRT page. A section “CAE Status Summary” is shown to the user based on cases below:

1. If the input object is up-to-date, then the CAE Status Summary just shows the following:

CAE Status Summary:
Status: Up-to-date
Last up-to-date timestamp: TIMESTAMP

2. If the input object is out-of-date due to dependent attachments, then Summary section provides that information as following:

CAE Status Summary:
Status: Out-of-date
Last up-to-date timestamp: TIMESTAMP
Out-of-date due to:
2 Dependent attachment(s) added
1 Dependent attachment(s) modified
3 Dependent attachment(s) removed

3. If the input object is out-of-date due to dependent ItemRevision objects, then Summary section provides that information as following:

CAE Status Summary:
Status: Out-of-date
Last up-to-date timestamp: TIMESTAMP
Out-of-date due to:
1 Dependent Item Revision(s) has a newer revision

4. If the input object is out-of-date due to multiple reasons, then Summary section provides all that information as following:

CAE Status Summary:
Status: Out-of-date
Last up-to-date timestamp: TIMESTAMP
Out-of-date due to:
2 Dependent attachment(s) added
1 Dependent attachment(s) modified
1 Dependent Item Revision(s) has a newer revision

ParameterInfo.description: Simulation dashboard configuration with query input details.

Operation.description:
This service operation asynchronously generates dashboard execution excel report.
Simulation Dashboard functionality is used to monitor the simulation data in the simulation dashboard table as per the simulation dashboard configuration which is configured by the user in the Teamcenter Rich Client. This service operation is used to get the simulation data as per the configuration saved under CAE0ConfigRevision object along with search query inputs to get the objects to monitor in the simulation dashboard. These objects to monitor are populated in the first column in the simulation dashboard table and the simulation data is populated in the subsequent columns for each object to monitor. Each row in the simulation dashboard table represents related simulation data for the object monitored. This service will provide support to get the paginated results in the simulation dashboard table. Simulation dashboard table is populated page by page on the scroll basis as per pageSize input with the help of indexing logic.
Operation.name: getDashboardDataByQueryAsync
Operation.returnDescription: As this is an asynchronous operation, it does not have return parameter.
Operation.useCase:
Use Case: When dashboard is loaded in the simulation dashboard location and user clicks the “Generate Dashboard Report” command then “Export to Excel” panel will get open. User clicks on “Generate Report” button on panel and excel report will get generated at the server and user will get notification with generated excel report link.

User clicks the “Simulation Dashboard” tile from home view in the Active Workspace client. System loads the simulation dashboard configuration objects in the primary work area. User selects the simulation dashboard configuration object (CAE0ConfigRevision) and clicks “Query Search” tools and info command. System opens query panel and user selects a query and enters the search criteria. User clicks on “Launch Dashboard” button on the panel. The system loads the simulation dashboard with simulation data as per the configuration. When dashboard is loaded in the simulation dashboard location and user clicks the “Generate Dashboard Report” command then “Export to Excel” panel will get open. User clicks on “Generate Report” button on panel and excel report will get generated at the server and user will get notification with generated excel report link. When user clicks on the notification link, excel report will get downloaded at client.

Operation.useCase:
User selects the CAE0SimProcessStatus object from the Progress monitor and clicks on “Process Files” command. The tcsimxml file that gets generated is then passed to the TTLC for the processing of the selected CAE0SimProcessJobDetails objects.
The status of the CAE0SimProcessStatus object can either be “Selective Import” or “Upload Conflict” governed by the output configuration of the CAE0SimTool object as defined in the Simulation tool configuration in the Rich Application Client.

1.    If the status is “Selective Import” on the CAE0SimProcessStatus object, the user is given an option to selectively import from the files chosen. The selected file is then uploaded to the CAEItemRevision object the tool was launched on.
2.    If the status is “Upload Conflict” on the CAE0SimProcessStatus object, the user can either rename the file or override the existing one and the renamed or the overridden file is then uploaded to the CAEItemRevision object the tool was launched on.

ParameterInfo.description: The CAE0SimProcessStatus object.

This input structure contains the user session information such as security token required for login, whether Single Sign-On (SSO) is enabled or not, SSO login URL, SSO Application ID, the host path representing the Active workspace server URL. This information is not validated.This information is embedded in the fmsTicket; which points to file: “openinsim.tcsimxml”.

If true, operation embeds this information in the fmsTicket; which points to file: “openinsim.tcsimxml”. Based on this, Teamcenter Tool Launch Client (TTLC) uses the Data Share Manager for upload of files; otherwise, operation continues using File Management System(FMS) for upload of files.

Use Case 2: User enables the Data Share Manager in Active Workspace client. Operation.useCase:
User selects the CAE0SimProcessStatus business object from the Progress monitor and clicks on "Process Files" command. The tcsimxml file that gets generated is then passed to the TTLC for the processing of the selected CAE0SimProcessJobDetails business objects.

The status of the CAE0SimProcessStatus business object can either be "Selective Import" or "Upload Conflict" governed by the output configuration of the CAE0SimTool business object as defined in the Simulation tool configuration in the Rich Application Client.

1. If the status is "Selective Import" on the CAE0SimProcessStatus business object, the user is given an option to selectively import from the files chosen. The selected file is then uploaded to the CAEItemRevision object the tool was launched on.

2. If the status is "Upload Conflict" on the CAE0SimProcessStatus business object, the user can either rename the file or override the existing one and the renamed or the overridden file is then uploaded to the CAEItemRevision object the tool was launched on.

Operation.description:
This service operation uploads the files on the client machine into the Dataset in the context ItemRevision based on selected files in the working directory and File Upload Rule Set provided on File Upload panel in context of the CAE objects (CAEAnaysisRevision, CAEGeometryRevision, CAEModelRevision, CAEResultRevision). File Upload Rule Set is a configuration object of the type CAE0ConfigRevision which consists of a set of File Upload Rules. A File Upload Rule contains information about the primary ItemRevision type, Dataset type, relation between the ItemRevision and the Dataset, named reference types, file naming patterns, dataset naming patterns. File Upload Rule Set also contains the information about Dataset creation options - As Needed, Always and Never. If the Dataset creation option is As Needed, then Dataset is created only when it does not exist in the context object. If it is set as Always, then new Dataset is created for every file upload operation. If it is set as Never, then if the Dataset exists, the files are uploaded in it; otherwise Dataset is not created.
This operation provides two ways to upload the files:
1.    Using the Data Share Manager (DSM): If user wants to use DSM, then output of this operation is used as input to the Data Share Manager(DSM)
2.    Without Data Share Manager: The files are uploaded in transient volume and using file upload tickets they are uploaded in Teamcenter. This is an asynchronous operation.
This operation returns FileUploadConflictInfo in the response if there are conflicts while uploading files using File Upload Rules. Conflicts can arise in two conditions.
1.    If the type of multiple context objects matches with the File Upload Rules primary ItemRevision type.
2.    If the name of the file to be uploaded matches with any of the files present in the Dataset.
This client uses the information present in FileUploadConflictInfo in the response to render the conflicts information to the user to resolve the conflicts.

Operation.description:
This operation creates multiple cloned or variant structures from the BOM structure by applying a Derivative Rule to it.
The output BOM structures may use the variant options set on the model BOMWindow or user can provide a set of variant options to be applied when deriving the output from input BOM structure. The output BOM structure is determined by the XSLT-based rules executed against the input BOM structure. These XSLT-based rules are a part of the Derivative Rule configuration. Several XSLT-based rules are defined under a Derivative Rule. There can be several Derivative Rules defined in the database by the user.

The output structures have a user defined name for the root, suffixed with a user defined numerical index which increments for each output structure created. Number of structures to be derived and the destination folder where output structures will be pasted are also determined by the user input.

Operation.description:
This service operation is called from Active Workspace Client which internally calls an asynchronous serive operation. It creates an output BOM structure given the root BOMLine of an input BOM structure along with a list of selected BOMLine objects. The selected BOMLine objects are processed to determine their parent and child BOMLine objects which form the complete selection and are used for processing. The BOMLine objects that are not a part of the selection are filtered out to create the output BOM structure. The output BOM structure is determined by the XSLT-based Data Map rules executed against the input BOM structure. Data Map syntax is in compliance with the schema defined in tcsim_xslWithNode.xsd, located in TC_DATA.

Data Map rules define the mapping between an input item type and its resulting output item type. Data Map rules are defined for an entire site and are stored in the datamapping.xml file located in TC_DATA. The name of the datampping file is defined by the site preference CAE_dataMapping_file.

The Data Map rules can be configured for various domains defined as LOV objects under Structure Map Domains in BMIDE. To configure the domains, in the Extensions view in BMIDE, open LOV->Structure Map Domains and add additional domain values. The domain to be used for applying Data Map rules can also be provided as an input.

To use this operation, a well-defined datamapping.xml is required in TC_DATA and the user should have either a simulation_author or rtt_author license.

OperationTemplate.description:
This service operation uploads the files on the client machine into the Dataset in the context ItemRevision based on selected files in the working directory and File Upload Rule Set provided on File Upload panel in context of the CAE objects (CAEAnaysisRevision, CAEGeometryRevision, CAEModelRevision, CAEResultRevision). File Upload Rule Set is a configuration object of the type CAE0ConfigRevision which consists of a set of File Upload Rules. A File Upload Rule contains information about the primary ItemRevision type, Dataset type, relation between the ItemRevision and the Dataset, named reference types, file naming patterns, dataset naming patterns. File Upload Rule Set also contains the information about Dataset creation options - As Needed, Always and Never. If the Dataset creation option is As Needed, then Dataset is created only when it does not exist in the context object. If it is set as Always, then new Dataset is created for every file upload operation. If it is set as Never, then if the Dataset exists, the files are uploaded in it; otherwise Dataset is not created.
This operation provides two ways to upload the files:
1.    Using the Data Share Manager (DSM): If user wants to use DSM, then output of this operation is used as input to the Data Share Manager(DSM)
2.    Without Data Share Manager: The files are uploaded in transient volume and using file upload tickets they are uploaded in Teamcenter. This is an asynchronous operation.
This operation returns FileUploadConflictInfo in the response if there are conflicts while uploading files using File Upload Rules. Conflicts can arise in two conditions.
1.    If the type of multiple context objects matches with the File Upload Rules primary ItemRevision type.
2.    If the name of the file to be uploaded matches with any of the files present in the Dataset.
This client uses the information present in FileUploadConflictInfo in the response to render the conflicts information to the user to resolve the conflicts.

OperationTemplate.description:
This service operation asynchronously derives multiple structures from the input with the given parameters and establishes a relation between input CAEModel structure and the newly created CAEModel structure.

The output BOM structures may use the variant options set on the model BOMWindow or user can provide a set of variant options to be applied when deriving the output from input BOM structure. The output BOM structure is determined by the XSLT-based rules executed against the input BOM structure. These XSLT-based rules are a part of the Derivative Rule configuration. Several XSLT-based rules are defined under a Derivative Rule. There can be several Derivative Rules defined in the database by the user.

The output structures have a user defined name for the root, suffixed with a user defined numerical index which increments for each output structure created. Number of structures to be derived and the destination folder where output structures will be pasted are also determined by the user input.

OperationParameter.description: The input structure to hold all the inputs for Generate CAE Structure service operation.
OperationParameter.name: generateCAEStructureInputs

OperationTemplate.description:
This service operation is called from Active Workspace Client which internally calls an asynchronous serive operation. It creates an output BOM structure given the root BOMLine of an input BOM structure along with a list of selected BOMLine objects. The selected BOMLine objects are processed to determine their parent and child BOMLine objects which form the complete selection and are used for processing. The BOMLine objects that are not a part of the selection are filtered out to create the output BOM structure. The output BOM structure is determined by the XSLT-based Data Map rules executed against the input BOM structure. Data Map syntax is in compliance with the schema defined in tcsim_xslWithNode.xsd, located in TC_DATA.

Data Map rules define the mapping between an input item type and its resulting output item type. Data Map rules are defined for an entire site and are stored in the datamapping.xml file located in TC_DATA. The name of the datampping file is defined by the site preference CAE_dataMapping_file.

The Data Map rules can be configured for various domains defined as LOV objects under Structure Map Domains in BMIDE. To configure the domains, in the Extensions view in BMIDE, open LOV->Structure Map Domains and add additional domain values. The domain to be used for applying Data Map rules can also be provided as an input.

To use this operation, a well-defined datamapping.xml is required in TC_DATA and the user should have either a simulation_author or rtt_author license.

StructElement.description:
Input method by which the Simulation Dashboard is executed.
Valid values are: "Query", "BOM", "Selected_IRs" and "Selected_Folders".
"Query" - The simulation dashboard is executed using the search query input panel on the simulation dashboard location from the client. Only CAEAnalysisRevision and CAEModelRevision objects and their subtypes are valid objects from the search query result as per the Simulation Dashboard configuration.
"BOM" - The simulation dashboard is executed from the CAEModel structure from the client.
"Selected_IRs" - The simulation dashboard is executed by selecting one or more objects from the client. Only CAEAnalysisRevision and CAEModelRevision objects and their subtypes are valid objects as per the Simulation Dashboard configuration.
"Selected_Folders" - The simulation dashboard is executed by selecting one or more objects of type Folder(s) from the client in the Analyst Workspace. Only CAEAnalysisRevision and CAEModelRevision objects and their subtypes from selected Folder objects are valid as per the Simulation Dashboard configuration.
StructElement.name: inputMethod

StructElement.description:
A map (string, string) with key as query attribute entry and value as attribute value from the search query panel in the Active Workspace client. It is used to perform search and get the objects to be monitored in the Simulation Dashboard.
For example:
